{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nrebar depends on the GitHub OIDC provider that snap's dead terraform owns, and the domain-wide wildcard cert + `auth_host` SSO stack are to be kept alive under rebar (user decision). All must move from snap's `snap-demo-tfstate` shared state into rebar's `rebar-tfstate` state, owned by rebar's `infra/terraform`. Physical names are preserved (rename = destroy/recreate); only ownership + tags move.\n\n## What\n**Provider declarations** (`infra/terraform/versions.tf`): add `hashicorp/random` (~> 3.6) and `hashicorp/archive` (~> 2.4) to `required_providers` alongside the existing `hashicorp/aws` — `random_password` and `archive_file` below require them, or `terraform init`/`validate` fail.\n\n**`infra/terraform/oidc.tf`**: `aws_iam_openid_connect_provider.github` (url `https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com`, client_id `sts.amazonaws.com`, thumbprint `6938fd4d98bab03faadb97b34396831e3780aea1`), `tags = { Project = \"rebar\" }`. Rewire `iam.tf`'s `gha_terraform_plan_assume` federated identifier to `aws_iam_openid_connect_provider.github.arn`.\n\n**`infra/terraform/acm.tf`**: `aws_acm_certificate.wildcard` (`*.solutions.navateam.com`, DNS), `aws_route53_record.cert_validation` (for_each), `aws_acm_certificate_validation.wildcard`. Cert gets `tags = { Project = \"rebar\" }` and `lifecycle { prevent_destroy = true }` (shared prod-critical). Validation records use rebar's existing `var.dns_zone_id`.\n\n**`infra/terraform/auth_sso.tf`**: SSO `locals` (auth_host, cookie_domain, google/cookie secret names, google_client_id, TTL). Manage `aws_ssm_parameter.cookie_signing_secret` at its EXISTING path `/auth-solutions/COOKIE_SIGNING_SECRET` with `value = \"CHANGEME\"` + `lifecycle { ignore_changes = [value] }` (rebar's ssm.tf idiom) — the live value is preserved on import and the Lambda reads it at runtime, so terraform never needs the value. DROP snap's `random_password.cookie_signing_secret` and the `data.aws_ssm_parameter.cookie_signing_secret` (only the edge-gate baking needed it; we do not adopt the sso-gate). Keep `data.aws_ssm_parameter.google_client_secret` (metadata only).\n\n**`infra/terraform/auth_host.tf`**: `random_password.auth_origin_secret` (KEPT — its value must be identical in the Lambda `ORIGIN_SECRET` env and the CloudFront custom origin header; imported with its LIVE value so both sides stay matched and nothing rotates), `data.archive_file.auth_host`, `data.aws_kms_alias.ssm`, `aws_iam_role.auth_host` + `aws_iam_role_policy.auth_host` (least-privilege, verbatim from snap: own log group + `ssm:GetParameters` on the two `/auth-solutions/*` params + `kms:Decrypt` via `ssm.<region>`), `aws_lambda_function.auth_host`, `aws_apigatewayv2_api/_integration/_route/_stage`, `aws_lambda_permission.auth_host_apigw`, cache/origin-request policy data sources, `aws_cloudfront_distribution.auth_host` (`lifecycle { prevent_destroy = true }`, viewer cert = the adopted wildcard), `aws_route53_record.auth_host_a` + `_aaaa`. Tag the taggable resources (Lambda, IAM role, API, CloudFront) `Project = \"rebar\"`.\n\n**Lambda source**: copy the live-deployed auth-host source from the snap checkout `~/snap-oakhart-manual/snap-oakhart-manual/infra/shared/auth/` — specifically `auth-host/index.js` (306 LOC) and `lib/cookie.js` (114 LOC), both verified present — into `infra/terraform/auth/auth-host/index.js` and `infra/terraform/auth/lib/cookie.js` (consumed by `archive_file.auth_host`). These are the exact files the live `snap-demo-auth-host` Lambda runs.\n\n**Name preservation**: `locals { legacy_name_prefix = \"snap-demo\" }` with a prominent comment that changing it destroys+recreates 18 live resources. Physical names stay `snap-demo-*`.\n\n## Live migration procedure (operator-attested)\nLive IDs (captured): OIDC `arn:…:oidc-provider/token.actions.githubusercontent.com`; ACM `…certificate/6597ee19-a770-4524-a0bd-fb86d608dd99`; Lambda `snap-demo-auth-host`; API `q8mv4bhkmh`; CloudFront `E15OTAFJILDOX6`.\n1. `terraform import` each live object into rebar state. Imports are idempotent and non-destructive; on partial failure, re-run the remaining imports (or `state rm` a bad one and retry) — nothing is destroyed until `apply`.\n2. Import `random_password.auth_origin_secret` with its live value read at import time from the live Lambda `ORIGIN_SECRET` env into a shell variable (never committed / not in HCL).\n3. `terraform plan` and iterate the HCL until the ONLY diff is the retag (drop snap default_tags `project/managed-by/root`, add `Project=rebar`) plus the incidental pre-existing `/rebar/prod/rebar-bot-signing-key` create. NO destroy/replace of adopted resources, NO secret-value change. Record the plan as a ticket comment.\n4. `terraform apply` (retag only). Then `terraform state rm` the 18 adopted resources from snap's `infra/shared` state, and remove/neutralize their HCL in snap's dead repo so its config cannot recreate them (snap is decommissioned; its drift CI is off).\n5. Post-migration health check: confirm `https://auth.solutions.navateam.com/authorize?return_to=https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com` still issues a 302 to Google and the CloudFront distro + Lambda are healthy (the stack must survive the ownership move).\n\n## Scope\nTerraform + Lambda source + live import/apply/state-rm only. Docs are child 6725. Does NOT adopt snap's `github_deploy` role, audit-dashboard sso-gate, ECS/ECR/VPC/RDS.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `versions.tf` declares `hashicorp/random` + `hashicorp/archive`; `aws_iam_openid_connect_provider.github` is in `infra/terraform` tagged `Project=rebar` and the drift role references its `.arn`.\n- [ ] Wildcard cert + auth_sso + auth_host resources exist in `infra/terraform` with physical names preserved, `Project=rebar` tags where supported, and `prevent_destroy` on the cert + CloudFront.\n- [ ] Cookie-signing SSM param is managed at `/auth-solutions/COOKIE_SIGNING_SECRET` with `ignore_changes=[value]`; the only remaining `random_password` is `auth_origin_secret`.\n- [ ] `terraform fmt -check`, `terraform validate`, and `make lint` pass on the new files; `infra/terraform/auth/auth-host/index.js` + `auth/lib/cookie.js` exist.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] All 18 resources imported into rebar state; `terraform plan` shows no destroy/replace and no secret-value change (evidence: plan output as a comment).\n- [ ] [operator-attested] `terraform apply` completed (retag); resources removed from snap's shared state; `https://auth.solutions.navateam.com/authorize` still returns a 302 to Google post-migration (evidence: outputs as a comment)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784046005871044001,"uuid":"22f8246d-3fae-4944-852e-ea390bd132c9"}